cells.data: Recursion: define a function that calls itself

Data Structures/Interfaces:

Set (AKA, Collections): no order, not a list, more of an object, no duplicates.
-ES6 contains native sets

Map (AKA, Dictionaries):  Key value pair

Stack: first in, last out. Only push, only pop, peek means just viewing the top of the stack.

Queue: First-in First-Out. Queueing in line. Can assign priority in a priority queue 

Array List: optimizes getting values. Expensive to deleting and shift values over.
Linked List: optimizes delete (don’t have to shift memory) but get’s are expensive.
